  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "The $(thing)Demon Realm$() are primarily built of an odd pale-blue material unknown in the rest of reality, aptly dubbed \"Demon Stone\" for what one would hope are self-evident reasons. Its construction seems quite simple, being an infusion of stone with a small amount of $(raw)Will$()."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone"
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_spread",
      "text": "This stone appears uniquely aggressive to material from our world; any attempt to mix Demon Stone and regular stone simply results in more Demon Stone."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_corrosive",
      "recipe2": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_destructive"
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_steadfast",
      "recipe2": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_vengeful"
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "Various coloured variants of this stone can be created by introducing stone to $(corrosive)Corrosive$(), $(destructive)Destructive$(), $(steadfast)Steadfast$(), or $(vengeful)Vengeful$() Will, as one may expect. As with $(raw)Raw$() will, they can be crafted in a stone cutter to all varieties of pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_corrosive_spread",
      "recipe2": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_destructive_spread"
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_steadfast_spread",
      "recipe2": "bloodmagic:dungeon_stone_vengeful_spread"
    }
  ]
